    "text": {
        "full_text": "The Lap Relay (Lappestafetten) is a knitted square / afghan block project released monthly by different designers. Participants cast on 50 stitches and knit flat using garter-stitch borders and a central charted or written motif. Techniques include yarn overs, slip stitches, k2tog, SSK-style decreases, textured stitches, and patterned repeats. The finished squares can be joined to make a patchwork blanket or used individually as cloths. Yarn and needle size are flexible based on preference, with examples including wool and cotton yarns such as Rauma Finull, Drops Safran, Hobbii Baby Cotton, Rauma Petunia, and others. Each square is finished with a garter border and loosely bound off, then blocked to shape. Pattern is available as a free Ravelry download in Norwegian.",
        "description": "A free monthly knitted square (afghan block) from Lappestafetten, designed to be used in patchwork blankets or as cloths."
    },
